No, no, no.

19:08.232 --> 19:16.723
What we know even intuitively, whether you're a person of faith or not, is that the value of a space dictates its level of exclusivity.

19:17.965 --> 19:19.026
The higher the value,

19:19.394 --> 19:20.615
the more exclusive it becomes.

19:20.696 --> 19:26.182
Paul is saying that your body is the most expensive real estate in the universe.

19:27.003 --> 19:32.169
Jesus died for it, the Holy Spirit lives inside of it, and God has an eternal purpose.

19:32.249 --> 19:35.774
Paul is saying that you don't have a body, you are a body.

19:36.695 --> 19:40.860
And because of Jesus, your body has become the holy of holies.

19:41.661 --> 19:49.330
Your goal shouldn't be to maximize pleasure through a lifelong joyride, hoping that you will not experience consequences, but that you are

19:49.410 --> 19:54.697
sacred, purchased with the blood of the creator of the universe.

19:55.839 --> 20:06.613
So if sex isn't gross, and if sex isn't a game, well, what we see is Paul shares with us that sex, it's actually a gift.

20:07.474 --> 20:16.146
Now, like any great, powerful, complicated gift, it requires understanding, it requires context, it requires instructions,

20:16.482 --> 20:23.432
See, that kind of power without understanding usually causes unnecessary pain, unnecessary problems and sex is no different.

20:24.133 --> 20:27.158
A simple way to think about this is to imagine a fireplace.

20:27.799 --> 20:32.025
Now, if you think about sex like a fire, fire is amazing.

20:32.085 --> 20:36.211
It can cook our food, it can keep us warm, it can literally sustain life.

20:36.591 --> 20:43.922
It's powerful and it's good, but this kind of fire belongs somewhere in our homes, somewhere in our lives, right?

20:44.002 --> 20:57.522
in a fireplace if we think about it in that context, or if we think about it inside of the context of relationship, this idea of sex as that fire belongs inside the covenant of marriage with one man, one woman with God at the center for a lifetime.

20:57.783 --> 21:01.128
That's the context that God universally gives us throughout the scriptures.

21:01.248 --> 21:04.313
Doesn't mean everybody always does it well, but that's the vision that God gives us.

21:04.633 --> 21:13.106
And it can serve as an essential purpose, but only when it's safe, only when it's life giving, only when it's in the proper context.

21:13.730 --> 21:22.323
So what happens if you like take the fire that's safe in the fireplace and you put it on the floor of your family room?

21:22.344 --> 21:25.088
Your house is gonna burn down.

21:25.108 --> 21:30.957
The late great Tim Keller used to say this, that true freedom is not the absence of restrictions.

21:31.718 --> 21:34.042
It's the presence of the right restrictions.

21:35.063 --> 21:39.250
A fish is only free when it lives inside the restriction of water.

21:39.714 --> 21:45.680
If you free it onto the counter next to the tank, it might have fewer restrictions, but it's going to die.

21:46.521 --> 21:49.023
And we oftentimes want to throw off all restrictions.

21:49.043 --> 21:50.364
That's not real freedom.

21:51.125 --> 21:52.486
Fire works this same way.

21:52.867 --> 21:58.172
In a fireplace, it's helpful, it's healthy, but outside of that, it isn't free.

21:58.252 --> 21:58.812
It's feral.

21:58.872 --> 22:00.814
It will consume everything.

22:01.775 --> 22:08.882
Remember the first week when we talked about the support beams of our house that we can't always see, but they provide an essential function?

22:08.994 --> 22:15.021
What Paul is saying is that sexual immorality is gonna burn those internal support beams to the ground.

22:15.842 --> 22:26.596
Last week, Javon talked to us about guarding our hearts that unrestrained sex, even if it's consensual, will rob you of something that God has for you that is so much better than that.

22:27.317 --> 22:31.562
We say from time to time around here is that when God says do, he means he designed you that way.

22:31.942 --> 22:34.946
And when he says don't, he means don't hurt yourself.

22:35.006 --> 22:36.668
God's not a cosmic killjoy.

22:36.688 --> 22:38.290
He's not trying to steal your fun.

22:38.722 --> 22:41.725
He's trying to keep your house from burning down.

22:41.765 --> 22:51.496
He loves you too much to let you play with the fire outside the context he made it for without at least warning you of the consequences that that will create.

22:52.577 --> 22:57.743
Now, I know that as I say all this, it lands very differently with very different people in the room.

22:57.763 --> 22:59.104
I totally get it.

22:59.124 --> 23:01.467
So I want to speak to three very different people today.

23:02.227 --> 23:06.492
First, to the single person that's listening to this right now, I want to be very clear.

23:06.532 --> 23:08.274
Singleness is not a waiting room.

23:08.962 --> 23:10.885
It is actually a gift.

23:11.686 --> 23:14.411
Paul, who we've been reading today, was single.

23:14.771 --> 23:17.255
This other guy you may have heard about was also single his entire life.

23:17.776 --> 23:19.359
His name is Jesus, okay?

23:19.379 --> 23:22.123
Like single is not a lower status.

23:22.384 --> 23:33.682
More than that, in the same letter that we've been reading, Paul calls singleness a gift because it gave him a level of undivided freedom in what God was calling him to do with his life.

23:33.954 --> 23:41.101
You have the capacity for kingdom impact and the freedom to serve right now that married people simply don't have.

23:41.962 --> 23:46.687
So don't confuse what you are experiencing as some sort of like relational purgatory.

23:47.488 --> 23:52.393
And I'm personally sorry for ways that if you're single and you're gonna, I think I'm okay, I think this is what God's called me to.

23:52.713 --> 24:01.362
I'm very sorry for the ways that people, that pastors, that churches either intentionally or unintentionally have made you feel less than as a result.

24:02.050 --> 24:08.340
But I also know that for some of you who are single, you actually desire to be in a romantic relationship.

24:09.061 --> 24:14.529
And so you're wondering about questions like, how do I find someone who's on the same path in life as me?

24:14.770 --> 24:19.337
Or maybe you found someone and you're dating and you're asking questions like, how far is too far?

24:19.918 --> 24:26.368
And for that one in particular, that's a little bit like asking, how close can I get the couch to the fireplace before it lights on fire?

24:27.089 --> 24:27.890
It's the wrong question.

24:28.386 --> 24:33.035
As a matter of fact, in the book Song of Songs in the Hebrew Scriptures, it's a book all about this.

24:33.636 --> 24:39.366
We get a picture of this, a picture of passionate, physical, and holy sexual intimacy.

24:39.907 --> 24:45.718
But three times in the book, we find ourselves where Solomon gives us this kind of form of advice.

24:46.519 --> 24:50.226
And in the first part, he says these words.

24:50.914 --> 25:13.042
promise me oh women this could also be then by the gazelles and wild deer like for all things holy please please please listen not to wake awake in love until the time is right he knows that there is something that fires up in you and me if we start this too soon as a matter of fact in the original language if we take this time is

25:13.186 --> 25:20.695
Right, really the words that we have there are the idea of seasons, that there is a season in your life that it makes sense for you.

25:21.015 --> 25:23.037
To say, hey, we're headed down this path together.

25:23.578 --> 25:25.440
God is honoring our relationship.

25:25.480 --> 25:26.822
Let's take these steps.

25:26.842 --> 25:36.353
And if God has placed in you a desire to experience marriage, it comes totally, normally, that He's also placed in you, a desire for this kind of fire, for sexual intimacy.

25:36.733 --> 25:40.978
But that fire needs a fireplace to warm you without burning you.

25:41.922 --> 25:46.068
So the better question might be, how do I honor the God who bought me?

25:47.170 --> 25:59.087
See, God, He's given you a season of freedom, even if you didn't ask for it, and I don't know how long it will be, but whether you are single for the rest of your life or just for this season, you are not a second-class citizen in the kingdom.

25:59.708 --> 26:04.655
God has a plan for you right now in all the circumstances you find yourself.

26:04.676 --> 26:06.098
Second is to the married people.

26:07.019 --> 26:11.826
Some of you, you have a fireplace, but it feels like the fire went out a long time ago.

26:12.898 --> 26:15.662
I'll just say this, mature marriage is they refuse to be roommates.

26:16.863 --> 26:21.009
We refuse to just drift to a place where we just sort of cohabitate.

26:21.069 --> 26:22.491
And I know how easy it can feel.

26:23.052 --> 26:25.556
Like you're passing in the night without much passion at night.

26:26.116 --> 26:28.660
You're managing logistics, kids, schedules.

26:28.720 --> 26:32.786
The trains are running on time, but you haven't paid attention to the fact that maybe they're on the wrong tracks.

26:33.627 --> 26:34.228
Hear me on this.

26:34.969 --> 26:37.472
Intimacy is spiritual warfare.

26:38.734 --> 26:41.778
The enemy of your soul hates your marriage.

26:42.626 --> 26:47.111
And he wants you to keep drifting, keep justifying it, keep rationalizing it.

26:47.492 --> 26:50.175
When sex is just a game, it will be easy to do that.

26:50.195 --> 26:53.559
When marriage isn't a covenant, but it's a contract, it will be easy to do that.

26:54.220 --> 27:06.134
But the most spiritual thing that you can do this week is maybe to begin putting fuel on the fire of the passion of your spouse by fighting the drift of apathy in your life.

27:06.894 --> 27:09.938
The great news, the great news,

27:10.018 --> 27:23.190
is that oftentimes with fires that have been going on for a long time, even when it looks like they're out, there's often embers at the base of the fire that can reignite and take less fuel than you think to reignite.

27:23.931 --> 27:31.698
And so for you, maybe this week, you're gonna take some steps about reigniting the passion that God has placed in your life.

27:32.279 --> 27:39.986
And yeah, this is probably gonna look like a gift, a meal, encouragement, and doing all those things without talking about your kids

27:40.450 --> 27:42.754
schedules or household responsibilities.

27:42.774 --> 27:44.236
It might even look like a foot rub, right?

27:44.256 --> 27:55.014
Like, whatever your spouse is going to process as genuine care and affection, trust God to reawaken the love through steady and kind presence without expectation.

27:55.495 --> 27:57.938
Steady and kind presence without expectation.

27:58.039 --> 28:06.032
If you're like, I said a nice thing, and they weren't instantly falling back in love with me, steady and kind presence without expectation.

28:06.072 --> 28:07.474
Trust God to move in their heart.

28:08.034 --> 28:21.454
Especially if you have what relational expert Dr. Gottman calls the four horsemen of the apocalypse in your marriage, here's what they are, contempt, criticism, defensiveness, and stonewalling.

28:22.215 --> 28:28.804
If those four live in your marriage, it's going to take some work because you did not get into this overnight and you will not get out of it overnight.

28:28.824 --> 28:31.068
But don't give up.

28:32.690 --> 28:35.474
Finally, I want to talk to the wounded and hurting in the room.

28:36.354 --> 28:44.143
This is really important because I know that some of you, the moment you found out what we were talking about today, you've been sitting here this entire time just like controlling your breathing.

28:44.844 --> 28:47.447
And you don't want anybody to see how heavy or hard this is for you.

28:47.747 --> 28:51.771
And in your heart, you're thinking, Phil, I've already burned the house down.

28:52.412 --> 28:56.277
Or maybe because of something that happened to you, you feel like somebody else burned your house down.

28:57.158 --> 29:01.422
Maybe you've made mistakes or someone's abused you and you're still in deep pain.

29:02.343 --> 29:04.626
I want you to know I'm so sorry for what you've been through.

29:05.282 --> 29:12.050
The consequences of sexual sin are so painful and often feel punitive, just like what Paul's talking about.

29:12.090 --> 29:13.892
They have a unique impact.

29:14.233 --> 29:19.279
But the good news of Jesus, the good news of the gospel is that it's a construction project.

29:19.299 --> 29:20.540
The God's not done.

29:20.580 --> 29:27.769
As a matter of fact, in 1st Corinthians 6 where we've been studying, right before where we've been studying, Paul talks about this very idea.

29:27.809 --> 29:30.031
He says, but you were washed.

29:30.932 --> 29:32.274
You were sanctified.

29:32.578 --> 29:38.447
You're justified in the name of the Lord Jesus Christ and by the spirit of our God.

29:38.487 --> 29:49.164
He's saying no matter what you've been through, it does not exclude you from the love of God, from the redemption, from the washing away of what's happened to you for a different life ahead.

29:49.865 --> 29:53.330
Culture is gonna tell you that your decisions, this is wild, right?

29:53.350 --> 30:01.202
It's a game where your decisions don't matter and then it flips and the decisions you've made have determined an inevitable direction and destiny, but that isn't true.

30:02.114 --> 30:03.255
You're not damaged goods.

30:04.357 --> 30:05.558
You're not a ruined house.

30:06.179 --> 30:09.944
You are the temple that has been washed by the blood of the Lamb.

30:10.625 --> 30:13.949
The graffiti is gone and the foundation is fixed.

30:14.570 --> 30:20.758
See, in a relationship with Jesus, which even if you don't have, you could start today, you are restored and being restored.

30:21.599 --> 30:24.903
God sees you as perfect even as He is perfecting you.

30:24.943 --> 30:30.450
Nothing you've gone through can ever make God stop loving you or pursuing you

30:31.234 --> 30:34.477
Church, our sexuality needs more than an appetite in 2026.

30:34.617 --> 30:36.279
It needs an anchor.

30:37.100 --> 30:40.243
It needs something more than guilt because it's actually a gift.

30:41.044 --> 30:49.432
God has given us boundaries as blessings even when they feel like burdens from the whispers of an enemy that hates you and wants to kill you.

30:50.953 --> 30:54.517
I know that for some of you, this teaching, it doesn't just feel hard, it feels offensive.

30:55.418 --> 30:58.000
You're sitting here and you're thinking, Phil, get out of my bedroom.

30:59.081 --> 30:59.922
Get off my phone.

31:00.994 --> 31:03.557
You want the comfort of the cross without the constraints of the covenant.

31:04.678 --> 31:05.119
And I get it.

31:05.839 --> 31:10.264
And again, if you're not a Christian and you want to continue to run the world's playbook, that's absolutely your prerogative.

31:10.284 --> 31:18.874
But if you are a follower of Jesus, I'm not going to apologize for giving you God's vision of sex because I've seen the wreckage of the alternative.

31:18.914 --> 31:19.735
I see it all the time.

31:21.096 --> 31:26.162
For me, even as a husband and a dad raising kids in a culture that sexualizes everything,

31:26.242 --> 31:31.047
I know that this is a war and you do not win a war by being passive.

31:31.628 --> 31:33.730
You don't win it by drifting into holiness.

31:34.011 --> 31:40.097
You win it by being ruthless with the things that are trying to kill your soul, that are trying to go after your kids.

31:41.479 --> 31:43.982
The world offers you a dumpster fire and calls it freedom.

31:45.483 --> 31:49.027
God offers you a fireplace and he calls it holiness, calls it freedom.

31:50.509 --> 31:52.892
One keeps you warm, the other is trying to burn you alive.

31:53.853 --> 31:55.154
So here's what you get to decide today.

31:56.066 --> 31:58.750
Which one of those fires are you gonna attend with your life?

31:59.952 --> 32:02.436
My encouragement, put the matches down.

32:03.597 --> 32:07.764
Stop playing with a fire that is designed to consume you outside of the covenant.

32:08.525 --> 32:10.067
Love is our foundation.

32:10.147 --> 32:12.110
Love is worth waiting for.

32:12.210 --> 32:15.415
And today, love is holy.

32:15.435 --> 32:22.886
It's holy because you were bought with a price because there's a life that God wants you to experience in abundance with him now.

32:23.207 --> 32:25.330
And in eternity later, you,

32:25.730 --> 32:27.272
are not your own.

32:27.332 --> 32:30.436
So we should stop living like we are.

32:31.737 --> 32:37.224
And my prayer today is that some of you are gonna pray with someone after the service and you're gonna share whatever you're comfortable sharing.

32:37.244 --> 32:39.347
We got people at all of our campuses ready to pray with you.

32:39.767 --> 32:44.713
You're gonna visit with a pastor or ministry member, ministry team member this week and talk about some things that are going on.

32:44.754 --> 32:48.258
Maybe they're gonna connect you to a counselor to start down this path.

32:48.278 --> 32:54.866
For some of you, you're gonna have a necessary but difficult conversation with someone in your life that you have been playing with this fire

32:54.946 --> 32:57.890
outside of the covenant with, and you're going to set some new boundaries.

32:58.872 --> 33:00.835
And those are all challenging conversations.

33:01.776 --> 33:08.266
But the idea that you can just keep playing this game without consequences, you know that's not true.

33:09.928 --> 33:16.879
So before we continue, before we thank God for who He is, before we think about all the other things that are coming with our day, would you pray with me?

33:21.105 --> 33:21.906
God, I know that

33:22.818 --> 33:24.821
This is such a deeply personal subject.

33:25.842 --> 33:29.146
For some, this is like the one thing we hope no one ever talks about.

33:30.007 --> 33:38.538
And we live in a culture where this struggle has become available, anonymous, free, all the time.

33:39.719 --> 33:45.266
And we are living so divided, we're living with this lie that we can

33:45.730 --> 33:53.020
live this individual picture of no restrictions and try to follow you and we are feeling it tearing us apart.

33:54.202 --> 33:55.423
So God, thank you for your grace.

33:56.525 --> 33:58.528
Thank you for the grace that allows us to come before you.

33:58.588 --> 34:04.015
Thank you for the grace that allows us to even tell someone about this and still know that we're loved, still know that there's a future in you.

34:06.539 --> 34:08.481
God, thank you for this kind of community.

34:09.082 --> 34:14.930
I pray that it would be one where your grace might be made manifest no matter what's been done to us or what we have done ourselves.

34:15.746 --> 34:19.437
Thank you for the gift of hope, even in the midst of all the hurts of this world.

34:20.461 --> 34:21.564
Would you show us that hope now?

34:22.647 --> 34:23.530
In Jesus name.

34:24.654 --> 34:25.436
Amen.

